Definition.WordDefinition: Outdated \Out*dat"ed\, a. Being out of date; antiquated; outmoded; unfashionable. [Obs.] --Hammond. [1913 Webster]

outdated adj : old; no longer in use or valid or fashionable; "obsolete words"; "an obsolete locomotive"; "outdated equipment"; "superannuated laws"; "out-of-date ideas" [syn: {obsolete}, {out-of-date}, {superannuated}]
